history.content:
Many of the students currently waitlisted for 160 (over 70) are declared cs majors.  The remaining slots are being held pending both confirmation of TA hires sufficient to support the projected final enrollment and also until the instructor determines how many of the spaces will go to graduate students in COMPSCI 260A.
Hopefully, it will work out but you definitely need a back-up plan just in case.

Hello! I recently declared computer science. In an email from cs advising, it informed us that we didn't have to do anything to get off the waitlist for open classes. Currently, both my lecture and section for 160 are open but I'm still on the waitlist. Does it normally take a week or two for the waitlist to process newly declared students?
history.subject: Recently Declared, Getting Off 160 Waitlist
